{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Dakshin punjab Bijli Vitran Nigam Limited |type = [[Electric utility]] |nativename = |nativename_a = {{Lang|hi|à¤¦à¤à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤£ à¤¹à¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¤£à¤¾ à¤¬à¤¿à¤à¤²à¥ à¤µà¤¿à¤¤à¤°à¤£ à¤¨à¤¿à¤à¤®}} |nativename_r = |logo = DHBVN Logo.jpg |logo_width = 160 px |logo_caption = Logo of DHBVN |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = {{Start date|df=yes|1999|07|01}} |preceding1 = Haryana Vidyut Prasaran Nigam Limited |preceding2 = Haryana State Electricity Board |jurisdiction = [[#Jurisdiction|See listing]] |headquarters = [[Hisar (city)|Hisar]], [[Haryana]], India |coordinates = {{Coord|29|48|27|N|75|48|04|E|type:landmark_region:IN-HR|display=title}} |motto = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = Manohar Lal Khattar |minister1_pfo = [[Chief Minister]] |chief1_name = Manohar Lal |chief1_position = [[Chief Minister]] |agency_type = |parent_department = [[Government of Haryana|Department of Power, Government of Haryana]] |website = {{URL|dhbvn.org.in}} }}
'''Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam''', also known as '''DHBVN Limited''' is an [[India]]n state owned [[electric utility]] company. It is owned by [[Government of Haryana]] and its headquarters is located in [[Hisar (city)|Hisar city]] of [[Haryana]], [[India]].<ref name=address>{{cite web |title=Address of various offices under DHBVN |url=http://www.dhbvn.com/main/contactus/address/addresses.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119080725/http://www.dhbvn.com/main/contactus/address/addresses.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=19 January 2012 |publisher=DHBVN |accessdate=10 July 2012 |df= }}</ref>
==History== In 1998, Haryana State Electricity Board was divided into two parts, namely, [[Haryana Power Generation Corporation Limited]] (HPGCL) and Haryana Vidyut Prasaran Nigam Limited (HVPNL). On 1 July 1999, HVPNL was further divided into two parts, namely, [[Uttar Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam]] (UHBVN) and Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam (DHBVN). DHBVN is responsible for [[Power distribution|distribution of power]] in South Haryana.<ref name="power">{{cite web|title=Dakshin Haryana Bijli Vitran Nigam(DHBVN) - Department of Power|url=http://dhbvn.org.in/web/portal/deptt.-of-power|website=dhbvn.org.in|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>
==Jurisdiction== DHBVN is responsible for distribution of power in the following districts of Haryana:<ref name=power/> * [[Bhiwani district|Bhiwani]] * [[Faridabad district|Faridabad]] * [[Fatehabad district|Fatehabad]] * [[Gurgaon district|Gurgaon]] * [[Hisar (district)|Hisar]] * [[Mewat district|Mewat]] * [[Narnaul]] * [[Rewari district|Rewari]] * [[Sirsa district|Sirsa]] * [[Jind district|Jind]]
