'''Elizabeth Cushman Titus Putnam''' is an American [[conservation movement|conservationist]] who in 2010 won the second highest civilian award, the [[Presidential Citizens Medal]], and was the first conservationist to have ever won the honor.
<ref>[http://www.whitehouse.gov/photos-and-video/video/2010/08/06/citizens-medal-winner-elizabeth-cushman-titus-putnam?v=accessibility] {{dead link|date=September 2018}}</ref> She founded the [[Student Conservation Association]] in 1957<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesca.org/newsroom/sca-founder-elizabeth-cushman-titus-putnam-receive-2010-presidential-citizens-medal-first-c|title=Newsroom|website=Thesca.org|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> and served as its President until 1990.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/sunyesf/docs/2006-1|title=Inside ESF 2006-1|website=Issuu.com|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> Ms. Putnam graduated from [[Miss Porter's School]] in 1952<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.porters.org/ftpimages/301/misc/misc_67719.pdf|format=PDF|title=Miss Porterâs School Annual Report July 1, 2009 â June 30, 2010|website=Porters.org|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> and from [[Vassar College|Vassar]] in 1955.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://info.vassar.edu/news/2009-2010/100804-liz-putnam-white-house-award.html|title=Archive from Wednesday, August 4, 2010 - Vassar alumna Elizabeth Putnam â55 receives the 2010 Presidential Citizens Medal at White House ceremony. - News - Info - Vassar College|website=Info.vassar.edu|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> She currently resides in [[Shaftsbury, Vermont]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcchicago.com/news/local/President-Gives-2-Chicago-Women-Highest-Honors-99929884.html|title=Obama Gives 2 Chicago Women Citizen's Medals|website=Nbcchicago.com|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> and the Vermont legislature passed act R-107 in her honor.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/55079276/Untitled# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2017-09-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108161529/http://www.scribd.com/doc/55079276/Untitled# |archive-date=2012-11-08 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

